AB  - The proceedings contain 27 papers. The special focus in this conference is on High Performance Computing. The topics include: Running a pre-exascale, geographically distributed, multi-cloud scientific simulation; Desynchronization and Wave Pattern Formation in MPI-Parallel and Hybrid Memory-Bound Programs; Understanding HPC benchmark performance on intel broadwell and cascade lake processors; Timemory: Modular performance analysis for HPC; TeaMPI—replication-based resilience without the (Performance) Pain; pattern-aware staging for hybrid memory systems; Simplifying communication overlap in OpenSHMEM through integrated user-level thread scheduling; Communication-aware hardware-assisted MPI Overlap Engine; Reinit++: Evaluating the Performance of Global-Restart Recovery Methods for MPI Fault Tolerance; Scalable Hierarchical Aggregation and Reduction Protocol (SHARP)TM Streaming-Aggregation Hardware Design and Evaluation; Predicting job power consumption based on RJMS Submission Data in HPC Systems; HyPar-Flow: Exploiting MPI and Keras for scalable hybrid-parallel DNN Training with TensorFlow; time series mining at petascale performance; Shared-memory parallel probabilistic graphical modeling optimization: Comparison of Threads, OpenMP, and Data-Parallel Primitives; opportunities for cost savings with in-transit visualization; semi-automatic Assessment of I/O behavior by inspecting the individual client-node timelines—an explorative study on 106 Jobs; preface; FASTHash: FPGA-Based high throughput parallel hash table; embedding algorithms for quantum annealers with chimera and pegasus connection topologies; Solving acoustic boundary integral equations using high performance tile low-rank LU Factorization; DGEMM using tensor cores, and its accurate and reproducible versions; Using high-level synthesis to implement the matrix-vector multiplication on FPGA; Enabling execution of a legacy CFD mini application on accelerators using OpenMP; load-Balancing parallel relational Algebra; Sparse linear Algebra on AMD and NVIDIA GPUs – The Race Is On.
