AB  - The proceedings contain 45 papers. The topics discussed include: Who have got answers? growing the pool of answerers in a smart enterprise social QA system; improving business rating predictions using graph based features; improving business rating predictions using graph based features; user identification using raw sensor data from typing on interactive displays; teaching motion gestures via recognizer feedback; mimetic interaction spaces: Controlling distant displays in pervasive environments; towards facilitating user skill acquisition - identifying untrained visualization users through eye tracking; visualizing expert solutions in exploratory learning environments using plan recognition; time-offset interaction with a holocaust survivor; hierarchical route maps for efficient navigation; audio haptic videogaming for developing wayfinding skills in learners who are blind; comparison of speech-based in-car HMI concepts in a driving simulation study; and see what you want to see: Visual user-driven approach for hybrid recommendation.
