AB  - The proceedings contain 35 papers. The special focus in this conference is on Distributed Computer and Communication Networks. The topics include: Integrity, Resilience and Security of 5G Transport Networks Based on SDN/NFV Technologies; openFlow-based Software-Defined Networking Queue Model; A Hybrid Clustering-Based Routing Protocol for VANET Using k-means and Cuckoo Search Algorithm; intelligent Systems for Optimal Production Control of Unique Products; evaluation of Trust in Computer-Computed Results; Distributed Computing of R Applications Using RBOINC Package with Applications to Parallel Discrete Event Simulation; autonomous Infrared Guided Landing System for Unmanned Aerial Vehicles; analysis of Non-preemptive Scheduling for 5G Network Model Within Slicing Framework; cardiac Arrhythmia Disorders Detection with Deep Learning Models; the Importance of Conference Proceedings in Research Evaluation: A Methodology for Assessing Conference Impact; method of Analyzing the Availability Factor in a Mesh Network; Approximation of the Two-Dimensional Output Process of a Retrial Queue with MMPP Input; response Time Estimate for a Fork-Join System with Pareto Distributed Service Time as a Model of a Cloud Computing System Using Neural Networks; machine Learning for Recognition Learning of Control Systems for Autonomous Unmanned Underwater Vehicles of Events in Hostile Environments; information Spreading with Application to Non-homogeneous Evolving Networks; the Increasing of Resource Sharing Efficiency in Network Slicing Implementation; sufficient Stability Conditions for a Multi-orbit Retrial System with General Retrials Under Classical Retrial Policy; on Convergence of Tabu-Enhanced Quantum Annealing Algorithm; a Two Server Queueing Inventory Model with Two Types of Customers and a Dedicated Server; customer Experience Model for Communication Service Provider Digital Twin; algorithm of Finding All Maximal Induced Bicliques of Hypergraph; Algorithm for Calculating and Using the Characteristics of a Binary Image Intended for Implementation on RCE; the Automata-Based Model for Control of Large Distributed Systems; preface.
