AB  - Intersections are very complicated scenarios in today's urban traffic.With the development of V2X and autonomous driving technologies, an unsignalized architecture has shown great potential in guiding the vehicles in a more efficient way at intersections.The conflict-free vehicle scheduling has been pointed out to be the key factor influencing both traffic efficiency and fuel economy.This paper presents a hybrid quantum approach to find the optimal passing order of the incoming vehicles.We first extract a decisive de-conflicting problem from the original scheduling problem based on the graphical conflict analysis.Then a novel hybrid quantum annealing algorithm is proposed to solve this subproblem.Finally we utilize a lower-level controller to apply our approach in a complete conflict-free coordination of vehicles at the intersection and simulations are conducted to assess the actual performance of the proposed approach. © 2024 IEEE.
