AB  - A computer code SAWMOD was developed to simulate the sawtooth oscillation by making use of a cylindrical plasma transport code TRANPY. Two models, the reconnection model and the turbulent model, were employed to describe the sawtooth oscillations. The former is mainly used to analyze the sawtooth of high qa discharges, while the latter is applicable to the low qa discharges (qa<0.9). With the SAWMOD code, analyzed in detail were the temperature, density, particle and energy confinement time, sawtooth period and inverse radius for a typical discharge with high density in the HL-1 tokamak. The calculated results from the two models are in good agreement with those from experiment.
